WEBVTT

00:10.523 --> 00:12.221
[birds chirping]

00:18.444 --> 00:21.186
[goat bleating]

00:21.230 --> 00:23.710
[rooster crowing]

00:25.799 --> 00:27.758
[quiet snoring]

00:27.801 --> 00:29.803
[dog barking]

00:34.155 --> 00:36.157
[snoring]

00:37.420 --> 00:39.422
[insect buzzing]

00:48.213 --> 00:50.302
♪

00:53.610 --> 00:56.482
[grunting]

00:59.616 --> 01:02.140
[inhaling sharply]

01:02.183 --> 01:03.576
♪

01:11.236 --> 01:13.238
[moans]

01:16.937 --> 01:18.939
♪

01:33.824 --> 01:35.826
[panting]

01:52.582 --> 01:56.455
♪ Nadie me es fiel ♪

01:56.499 --> 01:57.978
[horn honking]

01:59.589 --> 02:01.895
-♪ Triste es mi vida ♪
-[grunts]

02:04.071 --> 02:07.423
♪ Sin un cariño ♪

02:10.208 --> 02:12.645
♪ Lloro en silencio. ♪

02:26.442 --> 02:28.095
Si?Yeah.

02:39.498 --> 02:41.674
[Primo speaks Italian]

02:41.718 --> 02:43.720
[sighs]

02:57.037 --> 02:58.474
He's gonna be back soon.

02:58.517 --> 02:59.605
You have to go faster.

02:59.649 --> 03:00.998
Wait. Wait.

03:01.041 --> 03:03.087
My legs are being
all weird. I...

03:03.130 --> 03:05.002
-I haven't walked in...
-Oh, no, no, no.

03:05.045 --> 03:07.483
Y-You don't understand
what will happen to me.

03:07.526 --> 03:09.528
Please, just a minute.

03:09.572 --> 03:12.096
[panting]

03:14.054 --> 03:15.578
[gasps]

03:20.974 --> 03:23.020
We have to go back.

03:23.063 --> 03:24.282
Quickly.

03:24.325 --> 03:25.457
I'm not going back.

03:25.501 --> 03:26.719
[Angelo speaks Italian]

03:26.763 --> 03:28.504
Listen,

03:28.547 --> 03:30.680
w-we'll say you got free,
and I brought you back, okay?

03:30.723 --> 03:31.507
No, no, no, no, no!

03:31.550 --> 03:33.378
Hey!

03:44.650 --> 03:46.870
PAUL III:
St-Stop! Fucking think!

03:46.913 --> 03:48.654
[panting]

03:52.397 --> 03:54.573
PAUL III:
He's not an idiot.

03:54.617 --> 03:56.662
How did I get out?

03:56.706 --> 03:58.359
Who's got the key?

03:58.403 --> 04:00.492
Huh? You or me?

04:00.536 --> 04:02.189
[panting]

04:02.233 --> 04:03.234
[Paul III spits]

04:07.368 --> 04:09.675
[whistles]

04:23.602 --> 04:26.387
Pri-Primo.

04:26.431 --> 04:29.129
Primo.

04:50.977 --> 04:52.979
[gas can thuds]

05:08.604 --> 05:09.692
No, no, no! Primo!

05:09.735 --> 05:10.954
[whimpers]

05:19.049 --> 05:20.703
No! No! No, no, Primo!

05:20.746 --> 05:23.270
No! No, no, no!

05:23.314 --> 05:26.273
[screaming]

05:30.277 --> 05:31.670
[horn honks in distance]

05:34.455 --> 05:36.457
[horn honks in distance]

05:42.333 --> 05:44.335
[horn honks]

05:50.471 --> 05:51.734
[sighs]

05:51.777 --> 05:53.779
[muttering in Italian]

05:58.523 --> 06:00.525
[car door closes]

06:08.141 --> 06:10.143
Ciao.

06:11.667 --> 06:13.669
Primo.

06:26.812 --> 06:28.858
[speaks Italian]

07:09.072 --> 07:10.856
[speaks Italian]

07:15.774 --> 07:17.776
[birds chirping,
insects buzzing]

07:29.832 --> 07:31.834
[panting]

07:35.751 --> 07:37.927
-We need to get to a phone.
-ANGELO: Shh.

07:37.970 --> 07:39.755
-PAUL III:
There must be houses somewhere.
-Shut up.

07:39.798 --> 07:42.061
What?

07:42.105 --> 07:44.063
[church bells ringing
in distance]

07:44.107 --> 07:46.109
No.

07:46.152 --> 07:47.980
No, no, no, no, no.

07:48.024 --> 07:50.374
What?

07:50.417 --> 07:52.419
The bells.

07:54.552 --> 07:58.338
PAUL III:
So? What about the bells? Huh?

07:58.382 --> 07:59.339
[cowbells clanging]

07:59.383 --> 08:01.385
[bleating]

08:10.481 --> 08:12.483
[church bells ringing]

08:17.923 --> 08:19.446
[speaks Italian]

08:23.668 --> 08:25.626
PAUL III:
Hey, hey.

08:25.670 --> 08:26.889
What's that about, the bells?

08:26.932 --> 08:28.804
ANGELO:
Getting everybody.

08:28.847 --> 08:30.153
What?

08:30.196 --> 08:31.807
[Angelo speaks Italian]

08:31.850 --> 08:33.634
Everyone knows.

08:33.678 --> 08:35.854
Everywhere.

08:42.034 --> 08:43.906
About me?

08:43.949 --> 08:45.037
Yeah.

08:45.081 --> 08:46.256
And about me.

08:59.399 --> 09:02.054
Everyone knows-- we get...
we get rescued, right?

09:02.098 --> 09:03.752
No rescue.

09:59.982 --> 10:03.028
[overlapping chatter]

10:08.773 --> 10:10.819
[grunting]

10:13.734 --> 10:16.955
♪

10:16.999 --> 10:19.305
[barking]

10:38.411 --> 10:41.153
[barking]

11:03.175 --> 11:05.656
[sighs]

11:14.360 --> 11:16.406
What are you looking for?

11:19.191 --> 11:21.150
That valley is where I lived

11:21.193 --> 11:23.108
with my nonna.

11:23.152 --> 11:24.153
My grandmother.

11:26.633 --> 11:28.635
You know what they do
to people who betray?

11:30.333 --> 11:32.161
Me?

11:32.204 --> 11:34.554
They kill me.

11:34.598 --> 11:36.861
Easy. No problem.

11:38.123 --> 11:40.212
The family...

11:40.256 --> 11:42.823
they are...

11:42.867 --> 11:44.651
they are cut.

11:44.695 --> 11:46.740
Invisible.

11:46.784 --> 11:48.873
Nobody talks to them.

11:48.917 --> 11:51.441
Nobody gives them food
in the market.

11:53.269 --> 11:55.401
They turn their face away.

11:55.445 --> 11:57.012
They spit.

11:57.055 --> 11:59.579
They are alone...

11:59.623 --> 12:01.625
until they die.

12:02.669 --> 12:06.108
And that will be my nonna.

12:07.500 --> 12:10.373
I'm sorry,
I didn't know about your nonna.

12:12.679 --> 12:14.420
Yeah.

12:14.464 --> 12:17.380
You're just the golden hippie.

12:18.424 --> 12:20.992
You don't know anything.

12:21.036 --> 12:23.212
[sighs]
We have to get down there

12:23.255 --> 12:26.215
-before this afternoon.
-Why? You got a plan?

12:26.258 --> 12:29.218
You know where we're going?

12:30.262 --> 12:32.699
All right, don't.

12:32.743 --> 12:34.919
[dogs barking]

12:38.967 --> 12:40.969
[men speaking Italian]

12:42.840 --> 12:44.842
[dog squealing]

12:46.278 --> 12:48.324
♪

12:59.988 --> 13:01.946
[dog whining]

13:01.990 --> 13:03.730
[speaking indistinctly]

13:31.019 --> 13:34.326
Nothing in this country works.

13:34.370 --> 13:36.024
Nothing.

13:37.503 --> 13:40.289
I should never
have let you do it.

13:40.332 --> 13:41.768
CHACE:
$600...

13:41.812 --> 13:44.293
plus expenses.

13:44.336 --> 13:46.338
If they play their cards right,

13:46.382 --> 13:50.342
"plus expenses"
can be highly lucrative.

13:50.386 --> 13:53.084
I made that very clear to them.

13:53.128 --> 13:54.694
GAIL:
Expenses...

13:54.738 --> 13:57.436
for a Getty?

13:57.480 --> 13:59.830
If I were a kidnapper,
I'd be insulted.

14:01.701 --> 14:05.314
[sighs] I don't know why
I get talked into things.

14:05.357 --> 14:08.491
Every time.

14:08.534 --> 14:10.928
You...

14:10.971 --> 14:13.104
Paul, Lang.

14:13.148 --> 14:15.672
Let the men deal with it,
we'll sort it out.

14:15.715 --> 14:17.717
And this is what happens.

14:17.761 --> 14:20.372
It's an opening offer

14:20.416 --> 14:22.244
in a negotiation.

14:22.287 --> 14:24.985
They're considering
their position.

14:25.029 --> 14:27.249
They'll get back to us
in their own...

14:27.292 --> 14:28.989
Italian time.

14:29.033 --> 14:30.861
-Except they haven't.
-Yet.

14:34.082 --> 14:37.302
They didn't take Little Paul
for his good company.

14:38.956 --> 14:42.568
They took him 'cause they want
his granddad's money.

14:42.612 --> 14:45.571
They'll be in touch.

14:45.615 --> 14:48.139
Logically, it just makes sense.

14:48.183 --> 14:50.359
You think life's logical, Chace?

14:50.402 --> 14:52.404
[scoffs] Well,
if there's money on the table,

14:52.448 --> 14:54.363
more often than not.

14:54.406 --> 14:56.365
Don't you?

14:56.408 --> 14:57.801
No.

14:59.411 --> 15:01.109
[man speaking Italian on TV]

15:46.458 --> 15:48.112
Um...

16:14.182 --> 16:16.445
[reporters shouting in Italian]

16:19.535 --> 16:21.624
♪

16:31.851 --> 16:33.375
[crying]

16:33.418 --> 16:35.246
PAUL III:
Oh, man, I'm starving.

16:35.290 --> 16:37.509
ANGELO:
Uh, how do you call this?

16:37.553 --> 16:39.468
Black... Blackberries?

16:39.511 --> 16:41.078
Yeah, blackberries.

16:41.121 --> 16:43.385
[birds chirping]

16:45.517 --> 16:47.606
They're not ripe.

16:47.650 --> 16:51.044
Hey, where'd you learn English?

16:51.088 --> 16:53.525
School.

16:53.569 --> 16:55.440
Yeah, but it's-it's good.

16:55.484 --> 16:57.399
You know, the others,

16:57.442 --> 16:59.227
they didn't speak a word.

17:01.098 --> 17:03.187
You know the clever kid
in the class?

17:03.231 --> 17:05.058
Was me.

17:05.102 --> 17:07.409
I got sent to... to Napoli.

17:07.452 --> 17:09.498
Yeah.
Very fucking clever.

17:09.541 --> 17:12.196
[men shouting and dogs barking
in distance]

17:16.592 --> 17:18.071
Come on, run.

17:18.115 --> 17:20.335
♪

17:20.378 --> 17:23.294
[dogs barking]

17:23.338 --> 17:25.470
[men shouting]

17:26.471 --> 17:28.473
[dogs barking]

17:44.228 --> 17:45.447
Here, here.

17:45.490 --> 17:48.363
-Why?
-We lose the scent.

17:55.587 --> 17:57.589
♪

18:00.984 --> 18:03.552
-[whispers]: We should run.
-Shh.

18:03.595 --> 18:06.511
They've lost our scent.
It's okay.

18:14.432 --> 18:16.434
[train whistles in distance]

18:21.570 --> 18:22.832
Go that way.

18:22.875 --> 18:24.747
Trust me. Go that way.

18:27.837 --> 18:29.534
[dogs barking]

18:31.623 --> 18:33.059
[man speaking Italian]

18:37.194 --> 18:40.197
[train whistle blowing]

18:47.204 --> 18:49.467
[panting]

18:54.864 --> 18:56.909
Come on.

19:05.048 --> 19:07.485
♪

19:09.008 --> 19:11.359
[grunts]

19:14.449 --> 19:16.668
Take my hand!
Take my hand!

19:18.670 --> 19:20.455
[Angelo screams]

19:21.107 --> 19:22.370
[grunting]

19:31.727 --> 19:35.295
I thought...
I thought I was dead.

19:35.339 --> 19:37.994
Where I go, you go, right?

19:38.037 --> 19:40.126
Yeah.

19:41.171 --> 19:43.216
We got out!

19:43.260 --> 19:46.306
We really did it.

19:46.350 --> 19:47.656
[groaning]

19:47.699 --> 19:50.093
Oh!

19:50.136 --> 19:52.704
You're a genius, man.

19:52.748 --> 19:55.185
You're a genius.

19:57.753 --> 20:00.146
[dogs barking]

20:05.630 --> 20:07.458
[hissing]

20:09.547 --> 20:11.506
PAUL III:
It looks bad, man.

20:11.549 --> 20:13.508
I will be okay.

20:13.551 --> 20:15.945
Let's just get to Napoli.
We'll be safe in the city.

20:15.988 --> 20:18.077
-Get you to a doctor.
-No, too much...

20:18.121 --> 20:19.514
family in Napoli.

20:19.557 --> 20:22.386
I have to go to Rome and...

20:22.430 --> 20:24.083
disappear.

20:24.127 --> 20:26.521
What? No, no, no, no.
You won't be safe there.

20:26.564 --> 20:28.610
You're gonna come
to New York with me.

20:28.653 --> 20:30.568
Me? In New York?

20:30.612 --> 20:32.222
Yeah, you'll love it, man.

20:33.571 --> 20:37.096
I think you...
you will not want to know me

20:37.140 --> 20:39.534
when you're
with your famous friends.

20:39.577 --> 20:41.971
What are you talking about?
You saved my life.

20:43.320 --> 20:44.887
No.

20:44.930 --> 20:47.629
-You saved my life.
-Exactly.

20:47.672 --> 20:49.195
We're brothers now.

20:49.239 --> 20:51.328
I told you, man--
where I go, you go.

21:01.033 --> 21:02.513
Angelo.

21:02.557 --> 21:04.210
What?

21:04.254 --> 21:05.342
Angelo.

21:05.385 --> 21:08.214
It's my name.

21:08.258 --> 21:09.955
Angelo.

21:11.000 --> 21:13.481
Angelo.

21:15.004 --> 21:18.050
Well, it's a pleasure
to meet you, Angelo.

21:22.228 --> 21:24.230
[dogs barking,
men speaking Italian]

21:50.822 --> 21:52.563
♪

22:11.539 --> 22:12.975
PAUL III:
You know what?

22:13.018 --> 22:17.719
Just a juicy green apple.

22:17.762 --> 22:19.155
Apple? That's it?

22:19.198 --> 22:20.809
-Yeah.
-Crazy.

22:20.852 --> 22:22.288
Chicken and fries.

22:22.332 --> 22:23.594
Yes, yeah.

22:23.638 --> 22:25.596
Chicken...

22:25.640 --> 22:28.207
chicken cooked
in lemon and rosemary,

22:28.251 --> 22:30.035
like my nonna cooks.

22:34.257 --> 22:36.433
I will never see her again.

22:37.434 --> 22:38.653
Yeah, you will.

22:38.696 --> 22:40.655
We'll bring her to America.

22:40.698 --> 22:42.874
She can be our cook.

22:42.918 --> 22:45.442
-You think you can do that?
-Uh-huh.

22:45.485 --> 22:47.618
Like a magic trick?

22:47.662 --> 22:50.490
The Gettys can pretty much
do anything, man.

22:50.534 --> 22:53.493
Except pay for their son.

22:53.537 --> 22:55.670
[Paul III chuckles]

22:55.713 --> 22:57.715
Yeah, except that.

23:06.811 --> 23:09.553
♪

23:55.773 --> 23:57.122
Nothing on the ticker tape?

23:58.123 --> 24:00.212
Not about Paul.

24:01.779 --> 24:05.174
A five-pound check
from a woman in Exeter.

24:05.217 --> 24:08.743
Another from a lady in Scotland;
her pension for the week.

24:08.786 --> 24:11.049
And a 50-pence postal order

24:11.093 --> 24:12.964
from a...

24:13.008 --> 24:15.053
Nigel Stokes of Halifax.

24:15.097 --> 24:16.968
50 pence?

24:17.012 --> 24:19.623
It's his pocket money,
to help you with the ransom.

24:19.667 --> 24:21.799
I didn't say I couldn'tpay it.

24:21.843 --> 24:23.279
I said I wouldn't.

24:23.322 --> 24:24.933
There's a difference.

24:24.976 --> 24:25.760
Nigel's eight.

24:26.804 --> 24:29.546
-Send it back.
-Really?

24:29.589 --> 24:31.766
You never know when 50 pence
might come in handy.

24:34.986 --> 24:37.162
Bullimore.

24:38.990 --> 24:40.775
Bullimore!

24:40.818 --> 24:43.386
Immediately, sir!

24:49.000 --> 24:51.786
Are you going deaf?

24:51.829 --> 24:52.917
Not to my knowledge, sir.

24:52.961 --> 24:56.442
Then why do I have
to shout for you every time?

24:56.486 --> 24:58.793
[Paul sighs]

25:05.843 --> 25:08.193
[sighs]

25:08.237 --> 25:11.153
Why won't they make
a counteroffer?

25:11.196 --> 25:14.025
What's wrong with them?

25:24.035 --> 25:25.733
Huh?

25:33.741 --> 25:36.613
Primo.

25:36.656 --> 25:38.658
Che?

25:41.618 --> 25:43.620
Huh?

25:49.452 --> 25:51.454
[speaks Italian]

27:20.369 --> 27:22.066
[train chugging]

27:56.753 --> 27:58.755
[vehicle approaching]

28:04.369 --> 28:05.370
Shit.

28:10.854 --> 28:12.073
Wake up.

28:12.116 --> 28:14.945
Are we still in Calabria?

28:14.989 --> 28:16.381
-Are we still...
-Shh.

28:16.425 --> 28:17.948
[men shouting in distance]

28:17.992 --> 28:19.558
We should go.

28:23.780 --> 28:24.912
ANGELO:
Go.

28:26.000 --> 28:28.567
[panting]

28:31.875 --> 28:34.008
[vehicles approaching]

28:52.722 --> 28:54.724
[Angelo hisses, groans]

29:01.296 --> 29:02.993
[both panting]

29:26.408 --> 29:28.410
[animal chattering in distance]

29:35.286 --> 29:37.027
[both panting]

29:37.071 --> 29:39.247
I need food and water.

29:39.290 --> 29:41.249
No.
[sniffles]

29:41.292 --> 29:42.990
Not safe.

29:45.079 --> 29:47.168
I can't go any further.

29:47.211 --> 29:49.083
I just can't.

29:49.126 --> 29:50.084
[sniffles]

29:50.127 --> 29:51.302
I know.

29:51.346 --> 29:54.001
[panting]

29:55.306 --> 29:57.482
You know what?

29:57.526 --> 30:00.050
Do what you want.

30:00.094 --> 30:02.835
I'm gonna go find a house.

30:02.879 --> 30:06.100
I'm gonna find a house,
some water, a phone.

30:06.143 --> 30:09.190
-That's what I'm gonna do.
-[panting]

30:09.233 --> 30:12.106
Hey... you want to kill us?!

30:12.149 --> 30:15.544
Hey!
[panting]

30:20.027 --> 30:21.941
[whimpers]

30:24.335 --> 30:27.077
[inhaling deeply, sniffling]

30:27.121 --> 30:29.297
[panting]

30:33.214 --> 30:34.432
[sniffles]

30:34.476 --> 30:37.000
[panting]

30:53.973 --> 30:55.932
[insects buzzing]

31:22.350 --> 31:24.874
♪

31:33.883 --> 31:35.885
[grunting]

31:39.628 --> 31:41.151
-Here, here, here, here, here.
-[groans]

31:41.195 --> 31:43.284
[panting]

31:43.327 --> 31:45.155
-You all right?
-Yeah.

31:45.199 --> 31:46.156
[exhales]

31:46.200 --> 31:47.201
Come on.

31:49.638 --> 31:52.989
[grunts, panting]

31:56.775 --> 31:59.387
[vehicle approaching]

31:59.430 --> 32:01.389
[gasps]

32:07.003 --> 32:08.961
It's okay, let's go.

32:09.005 --> 32:11.399
Let's keep on going.

32:14.402 --> 32:17.361
[panting]

32:26.327 --> 32:29.721
[creaking]

32:32.942 --> 32:35.162
-[loud clang]
-[gasps]

32:37.903 --> 32:40.036
Where is everybody?

32:45.868 --> 32:48.392
-Come on.
-[clattering]

32:50.177 --> 32:52.396
[whispers]:
Come on.

32:54.398 --> 32:56.357
No, no, no.

32:56.400 --> 32:57.445
[jiggles doorknob,
knocks on door]

32:57.488 --> 32:59.490
[cat meowing]

33:03.320 --> 33:04.321
[thumping]

33:09.152 --> 33:10.197
[loud clattering]

33:12.982 --> 33:14.984
[exhales, sniffles]

33:34.221 --> 33:36.223
[breathing heavily]

34:05.121 --> 34:07.123
[dialing continues]

34:15.479 --> 34:18.003
[dialing continues]

34:21.355 --> 34:23.531
-Come on, Mom.
-[line rings]

34:23.574 --> 34:25.054
[dogs barking in distance]

34:31.800 --> 34:34.542
-[line ringing]
-Come on.

34:34.585 --> 34:37.153
[phone ringing]

34:40.983 --> 34:43.507
[dogs barking outside]

34:44.856 --> 34:47.381
[men chattering]

34:47.424 --> 34:49.687
-[dogs barking]
-[knocking]

34:49.731 --> 34:50.732
[man shouts]

34:52.777 --> 34:56.346
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey. Hey.

34:56.390 --> 34:58.566
-[panting]: They're here.
-It's ringing.

34:58.609 --> 35:00.219
-It's ringing.
-They're here!

35:00.263 --> 35:01.830
[grunts]

35:01.873 --> 35:03.614
-[phone ringing]
-[clanking]

35:03.658 --> 35:06.487
Hello? Hello?

35:09.533 --> 35:11.535
[dogs barking]

35:28.422 --> 35:30.424
Paul?

35:31.642 --> 35:34.253
Paul?

35:34.297 --> 35:36.821
Paul, is that you?

35:36.865 --> 35:39.694
Paul, it's Mom.

35:41.478 --> 35:44.786
Paul, speak to me.

35:44.829 --> 35:46.657
Are you okay?

35:46.701 --> 35:48.224
[mockingly]:
Paul.

35:48.267 --> 35:50.748
Paul.

35:50.792 --> 35:52.881
Who is this?

35:52.924 --> 35:54.012
Si, Paul.

35:54.056 --> 35:55.231
[gasps]

36:01.106 --> 36:04.501
[panting]

36:04.545 --> 36:06.851
[dogs barking]

36:06.895 --> 36:09.419
♪

36:25.870 --> 36:27.350
[dogs barking]

36:33.051 --> 36:35.140
[sniffs]

36:40.363 --> 36:42.409
[sniffs]

37:10.872 --> 37:13.352
♪

37:41.685 --> 37:43.557
♪

37:54.785 --> 37:57.179
♪

38:23.814 --> 38:26.382
♪

38:40.831 --> 38:42.920
[truck door opening]

38:42.964 --> 38:44.966
[goats bleating]

39:02.418 --> 39:03.811
[rooster crowing]

39:09.338 --> 39:11.340
-Hey.
-Hi.

39:13.690 --> 39:15.344
Uh...
[sniffs]

39:27.312 --> 39:29.271
Eh?

39:29.314 --> 39:31.534
Uh...

39:36.887 --> 39:38.193
What?

39:38.236 --> 39:39.237
Hey.

39:43.328 --> 39:44.852
[whispers]:
We should go.

39:44.895 --> 39:48.072
No, no, no. I call my mom
and then we're out of here.

39:52.555 --> 39:54.078
[rooster crowing]

39:54.122 --> 39:56.733
They'll send a fucking army
for us, okay?

39:56.777 --> 39:58.039
He's helping us, I know it.

40:08.266 --> 40:10.355
[whispers indistinctly]

40:11.356 --> 40:13.794
-Luigi.
-Hey.

40:18.059 --> 40:19.626
Ah.

40:20.714 --> 40:21.932
Mm.

40:37.731 --> 40:40.821
[goat bleating, rooster crowing]

40:40.864 --> 40:42.866
[Rosaria grunts]

40:56.880 --> 40:58.665
[whispering]:
It's not... it's not working.

41:07.978 --> 41:10.328
She thinks it was the storm.

41:18.989 --> 41:19.686
Uh...

41:27.476 --> 41:28.956
-ROSARIA: Paolo?
-Yeah.

41:31.001 --> 41:32.002
[sighs]

41:34.831 --> 41:35.702
[whispering]:
We should go.

41:40.924 --> 41:41.969
Eh? [laughs]

41:45.712 --> 41:47.409
-[speaks Italian]
-Ooh.

41:58.507 --> 41:59.813
[speaking Italian]

42:00.814 --> 42:02.816
[Angelo grunts]

42:06.080 --> 42:09.910
[quietly]:
There hasn't been a storm.

42:09.953 --> 42:11.955
[speaking Italian]

42:14.305 --> 42:16.307
[gasps]

42:18.875 --> 42:20.747
[music playing over speaker]

42:30.104 --> 42:31.105
[chuckles]

42:37.676 --> 42:39.678
[music continues]

42:45.075 --> 42:46.947
Grazie.

42:46.990 --> 42:49.253
[Angelo and Rosaria grunt]

42:52.735 --> 42:54.737
[sighs]

42:55.999 --> 42:59.437
Oh, no. Grazie.

43:28.118 --> 43:30.904
She says... she says, uh,

43:30.947 --> 43:33.210
he-he's gonna drive us
to the main road,

43:33.254 --> 43:36.083
and then-then we can hitch
to Napoli, no problem.

43:36.126 --> 43:37.911
What, now?

43:44.482 --> 43:46.484
-[goat bleating]
-[thunder rumbling]

43:51.794 --> 43:53.274
ANGELO:
Ah.

44:03.980 --> 44:07.157
Oh... okay.

44:07.201 --> 44:08.898
[bagpipes playing]

44:15.078 --> 44:16.427
[Rosaria sighs happily]

44:20.388 --> 44:22.346
PAUL III:
This is so good.

44:22.390 --> 44:24.087
ANGELO:
Yeah, my nonna-- she can cook

44:24.131 --> 44:27.134
capra alla bovese, frittole,

44:27.177 --> 44:28.135
caponata.

44:28.178 --> 44:30.789
[muttering in Italian]

44:35.142 --> 44:38.362
People here, they have nothing,

44:38.406 --> 44:40.843
but they're just willing
to give you everything.

44:40.887 --> 44:44.064
[muttering in Italian]

44:44.107 --> 44:45.630
Then I'm going to live
in a country

44:45.674 --> 44:47.937
where people have everything.

44:47.981 --> 44:49.112
It's gonna be great.

44:50.200 --> 44:51.593
[clapping]

44:51.636 --> 44:53.029
[Angelo laughs]

44:54.335 --> 44:56.206
A toast.

44:56.250 --> 44:59.383
-Yeah? To brothers.
-Yes. Yes.

44:59.427 --> 45:01.168
Oh, no, no, no.
We need more brandy.

45:01.211 --> 45:03.300
-Rosario!
-Rosaria!

45:03.344 --> 45:05.085
-Rosaria!
-[muttering]

45:05.128 --> 45:06.086
[door opens]

45:06.129 --> 45:08.697
[dogs barking outside]

45:10.220 --> 45:12.614
That's all, folks.

45:13.615 --> 45:15.138
PAUL III:
Hey, wait, wait, wait, wait...!

45:16.357 --> 45:17.532
No!

45:17.575 --> 45:20.143
-[gunshot]
-[glass breaking]

45:20.187 --> 45:22.189
♪

45:24.843 --> 45:27.194
♪ Ah♪

45:27.237 --> 45:29.936
♪ Ah...♪

45:32.242 --> 45:36.159
♪ If I give my heart to you♪

45:39.162 --> 45:42.687
♪ Will you handle it
with care?♪

45:45.255 --> 45:47.779
♪ Will you always treat me♪

45:47.823 --> 45:51.696
♪ Tenderly?♪

45:51.740 --> 45:55.613
♪ And in every way be fair?♪

45:58.877 --> 46:02.490
♪ If I give my heart to you♪

46:05.623 --> 46:08.975
♪ Will you give me
all your love?♪

